data.title: Hanging Rock State Park: Home
data.text:
Swimming at the lake is permitted between Memorial Day weekend and Labor Day weekend (May 25 through Sept. 2, 2024) during operational hours.

Mondays 11 a.m. to 5:30 p.m. Tuesdays Closed Wednesdays Closed Thursday 10 a.m. to 5:30 p.m. Friday 10 a.m. to 5:30 p.m. Saturday 10 a.m. to 5:30 p.m. Sunday 10 a.m. to 5:30 p.m.

Lake operational hours may vary due to staff availability. The diving platform may be closed due to lifeguard staffing; please inquire with park staff for hours.

A fee is charged for all swimmers. Free swim is available from 4:45 p.m. to 5:30 p.m.

Boat rentals are available between Memorial Day weekend and Labor Day weekend (May 25 through Sept. 2, 2024) during operational hours.

Mondays 11 a.m. to 4:30 p.m. Tuesdays Closed Wednesdays Closed Thursday 10 a.m. to 4:30 p.m. Friday 10 a.m. to 4:30 p.m. Saturday 10 a.m. to 4:30 p.m. Sunday 10 a.m. to 4:30 p.m.

Lake operational hours may vary due to staff availability.

The last rental is at 4:30 p.m. and all boats must be returned by 5:30 p.m. A fee is charged for all boat rentals and visitors must be at least 16 years old to rent.

Personal boats and watercraft are not allowed on the lake.
